31st March, 2026
----------------

Animated Flatlist with reanimated was a mistake it gives a jittery effect when switching slides
once carousel reaches end or user tries to go backwards, felt unnatural and bugged.
Im switching to react-native-reanimated-carousel for out of the box infinite carousel 
support and better performance.

1st April, 2026
---------------

Ripped out a ton of custom carousel logic since the library handles 
pagination and infinite looping natively — less code, fewer bugs, better 
perf. Win-win-win. Threw in some stagger animations on the text while I 
was at it, looks clean.

Fixed the size selector alignment on the product screen, was bugging me 
for a while. Also wired up default size selection on product load — 
falls back to whatever's flagged as default in the DB, or small if 
nothing's set. No more forcing users to manually pick a size before 
adding to cart, that UX debt is finally paid off.

Price now derives from selected size reactively across both the product 
screen and cart — state stays consistent, no stale values. 

Next up, nuking the DB and reseeding with proper size-based pricing baked 
in at the schema level. Tired of hardcoding prices client-side — moving 
to a single source of truth in the backend so pricing changes don't 
require a redeploy.

3rd April, 2026
----------------
Implemented adding address by location detection, I used expo-location to get the coordinates and 
then reverse geocoding to get the address details. Added a loading state for the detect location 
button to prevent multiple taps and indicate progress.
Testing with new tabs icon - probably will change again but wanted to try something different for a bit.
But a animated tab bar is for the v.2 release, want to get the core functionality down first.
Next is Profile Screen and then safe pay (50% chances).


*Last updated: April 2026*